cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.NE, cs.CV

The paper proposes a new pre-processing technique for balancing datasets using SMOTE and evaluates its performance on imbalanced datasets using classification algorithms. This work falls under the broad category of machine learning and specifically focuses on data preprocessing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses mutual information and different types of entropies to improve the performance of SMOTE, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The use of classification algorithms such as 1NN and J48 also indicates that the paper could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these sub-categories often use classification algorithms for image recognition and other tasks.
